01:47:39.256 --> 01:47:42.316
Until then, you stay
in the safety of the monastery.

756
01:47:44.088 --> 01:47:48.817
- And all this, because you had a bad dream?
- I've made my decision.

757
01:47:48.935 --> 01:47:53.191
- But I don't know whether I even love him!
- I'm afraid the circumstances leave us no choice.

758
01:47:53.272 --> 01:47:55.975
- Papa!
- It's all arranged, Laura.

759
01:53:45.955 --> 01:53:47.039
On your feet!

760
01:53:47.605 --> 01:53:48.646
Hands in the air!

761
01:54:34.626 --> 01:54:37.231
Why did you kill my daughter?

762
01:54:41.353 --> 01:54:42.449
Why?

763
01:54:45.759 --> 01:54:47.252
I needed her.

764
01:55:13.622 --> 01:55:15.957
Why did you kill my daughter?

765
01:55:20.408 --> 01:55:22.029
I just...

766
01:55:24.753 --> 01:55:26.286
needed her.

767
01:55:34.071 --> 01:55:35.388
Very well.

768
01:55:37.594 --> 01:55:39.917
But you remember this:

769
01:55:46.501 --> 01:55:48.399
I'll be looking at you...

770
01:55:51.054 --> 01:55:52.631
when you're laid on the cross,

771
01:55:52.696 --> 01:55:57.375
and the twelve blows are
crashing down on your limbs.

772
01:55:59.603 --> 01:56:05.236
When the crowd is finally tired
of your screams and wandered home...

773
01:56:06.456 --> 01:56:10.755
I will climb up
through your blood...

774
01:56:12.595 --> 01:56:14.869
and sit beside you.

775
01:56:16.515 --> 01:56:20.108
I will look deep
into your eyes...

776
01:56:21.144 --> 01:56:24.322
and drop by drop...

777
01:56:26.271 --> 01:56:30.280
I will trickle my digust into them...

778
01:56:32.023 --> 01:56:35.003
like burning acid...

779
01:56:36.822 --> 01:56:38.285
until...

780
01:56:41.810 --> 01:56:43.328
finally...

781
01:56:46.965 --> 01:56:49.085
you perish.

782
01:57:24.426 --> 01:57:26.015
What do you think
they'll do to him?

783
01:57:26.307 --> 01:57:30.194
Apparently, they're gonna break
every bone in his body with an iron bar.

784
01:57:43.574 --> 01:57:45.008
Look, there he comes!

785
01:58:48.920 --> 01:58:50.484
Unchain the prisoner.

786
01:59:01.952 --> 01:59:03.545
That's enough.

787
01:59:05.032 --> 01:59:07.035
Let him be brought
to the scaffold.

788
01:59:12.143 --> 01:59:13.110
What's that?

789
02:00:27.188 --> 02:00:28.980
Is he coming? What's his name?

790
02:02:19.047 --> 02:02:22.100
This man is innocent.

791
02:02:25.996 --> 02:02:28.815
- He didn't do it. It's impossible!
- He's innocent!

792
02:02:33.257 --> 02:02:34.537
He's innocent!

793
02:03:54.766 --> 02:03:59.127
This is no man!
This is an angel!

794
02:10:07.529 --> 02:10:09.839
You can't fool me!

795
02:10:58.639 --> 02:11:00.238
Forgive me!

796
02:11:06.900 --> 02:11:09.067
My son!

797
02:12:11.630 --> 02:12:15.619
People of Grasse
awoke to a terrible hangover.

798
02:12:16.937 --> 02:12:22.166
For many of them, the experience
was so gustly, so completely inexplicable...

799
02:12:22.199 --> 02:12:28.387
and incompatible with their morals,
that they literally erased it from their memories.

800
02:12:29.032 --> 02:12:32.027
The town council
was in session by the afternoon.

801
02:12:32.151 --> 02:12:38.307
And an order was passed to the police lieutenant
to immediately begin fresh investigations into the murders.

802
02:12:39.455 --> 02:12:42.488
The following day, Dominique Druot
was arrested.

803
02:12:42.575 --> 02:12:47.340
Since it was in his backyard that the clothes
and hair of all the victims had been found.

804
02:12:48.356 --> 02:12:51.785
After fourteen hours of torture,
Druot confessed to everything.

805
02:12:54.619 --> 02:12:57.281
With that, the case was closed.

806
02:13:01.648 --> 02:13:05.481
By then, Grenouille was already
halfway back to Paris.

807
02:13:09.461 --> 02:13:13.801
He still had enough perfume left
to enslave the whole world, if he so chose.

808
02:13:14.513 --> 02:13:17.754
He could walk to Versailles,
and have the King kiss his feet.

809
02:13:18.177 --> 02:13:22.713
He could write the Pope a perfumed letter,
and reveal himself as a new Messiah.

810
02:13:23.535 --> 02:13:26.594
He could do all this,
and more if he wanted to.

811
02:13:27.319 --> 02:13:31.956
He possessed a power stronger
than the power of money, or terror, or death.

812
02:13:32.747 --> 02:13:36.616
The invincible power
to command the love of mankind.

813
02:13:43.380 --> 02:13:46.269
There was only one thing
the perfume could not do.

814
02:13:46.666 --> 02:13:52.047
It could not turn him into a person
who could love and be loved like everyone else.

815
02:13:53.280 --> 02:13:57.193
So, to hell with it, he thought.
To hell with the world.

816
02:13:57.689 --> 02:14:00.715
With the perfume, with himself.

817
02:14:03.511 --> 02:14:08.797
On the 25th of June, 1766,
around 11 o'clock at night,

818
02:14:09.033 --> 02:14:12.249
Grenouille entered the city
through the port-de-Leones.

819
02:14:12.805 --> 02:14:19.807
And like a sleepwalker, his olfactory memories
drew him back to the place where he was born.

820
02:15:42.004 --> 02:15:44.838
An angel!

821
02:15:46.279 --> 02:15:48.265
I love you!

822
02:16:35.557 --> 02:16:41.289
Within no time, Jean-Baptiste Grenouille
had disappeared from the face of the earth.

823
02:16:42.332 --> 02:16:47.170
When they had finished,
they felt a virginal glow of happiness.

824
02:16:47.887 --> 02:16:53.182
For the first time in their lives,
they believed that they had done something...

825
02:16:53.426 --> 02:16:56.791
purely out of love.

826
02:17:27.539 --> 02:17:29.590
Hey, over here!

827
02:17:30.179 --> 02:17:31.174
Look!

828
02:17:38.497 --> 02:17:39.787
Let's take them away.

829
02:17:40.600 --> 02:17:41.760
You could wear them.

